        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 4:21PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Summersville, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Summersville, Canvas, and Mount Nebo.

This includes Route 19 between mile markers 35 and 41.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
